<br>
They're situational, they're great for botting 3 because I don't have to remember to sit to med after casting spells, also because the cleric can med through complete heals.  They're just nice for mana regen in general since you're always medding.  Obviously useless indoors and you need to get real fast at typing /dism when you start casting the wrong spell or you're getting beaten on and you need to back up.  I have it hotkeyed of course but you can't use hotkeys while casting, you need to type it in.<br>
<br>
I find them especially useful soloing high-HP mobs like Umbral Plains mobs... the fights may be minutes long and I can sit on my horse and nuke/med throughout without ever getting any sitting aggro.  They're also useful in Maiden's groups where I'm not pulling, because I can just nuke &amp; med at the same time without having to sit/stand all the time.<br>
<br>
I'd say they are more useful for clerics, shamans and enchanters because they can debuff mobs or heal, then med without getting sitting aggro.<br>
<br>
I don't have mine for travel speed (have RS 3 and SoW potions for that) but they're worth the 9.5k (black/white rope bridles) to me just for the situational mana regen. <p>-- <BR>
